["form of the biblical Hebrew name <i>Yosef</i>, meaning ‘(God) shall add (another son)’. This was borne by the favourite son of Jacob, whose brothers became jealous of him and sold him into slavery (Genesis 37). He was taken to Egypt, where he rose to become chief steward to Pharaoh, and was eventually reconciled to his brothers when they came to buy corn during a seven-year famine (Genesis 43–7). In the New Testament <i>Joseph</i> is the name of the husband of the Virgin Mary. It is also borne by a rich Jew, Joseph of Arimathea (Matthew 27:57; Mark 15:43; Luke 23:50; John 19:38), who took Jesus down from the Cross, wrapped him in a shroud, and buried him in a rock tomb. According to medieval legend, Joseph of Arimathea brought the Holy Grail to Britain. The name was uncommon in Britain in the Middle Ages but was revived in the mid 16th century and had become popular by the 1630s, remaining so ever since."],"variants":[{"name":"Josef","meanings":[", Dutch, Scandinavian, and Czech spelling of   Joseph  , now also in use in the English‐speaking world."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705182,"age":1,"year":"1066","julianDay":2110409,"title":"Battle of Hastings","description":"Battle of Hastings was fought between the Norman-French army and the battle-wary English army on October 14, 1066. Duke William of Normandy believed he was the rightful king rather than Harold, who had been crowned king several months earlier. Harold was killed in battle and William was crowned king on Christmas Day 1066.","url":"https://www.english-heritage.org.uk/learn/1066-and-the-norman-conquest/what-happened-battle-hastings/","urlTitle":"English Heritage - Battle of Hastings","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705183,"age":21,"year":"1086","julianDay":2117714,"title":"Domesday Book","description":"Domesday Book is Britain's earliest extant public record with information containing land surveys and landholdings commissioned by William I. The book was completed in 1086.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/domesday/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Domesday","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705184,"age":31,"year":"1096","julianDay":2121366,"title":"The Crusades","description":"A series of religious wars between Christians and Muslims, known as the Crusades, occurred between 1096 and 1291, and played a large role in European Christian dominance in the Middle East.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/middle-ages/crusades","urlTitle":"History - The Crusades","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Joseph was born about 1065, in England. She had at least 1 daughter with Joseph. She died in her hometown."},"et":{"about 1065–":"umbes 1065–Surnud","1060–Male":"1060–Surnud","1080–Female":"1080–Surnud","1065–Female":"1065–Surnud","1080":"1080","1066":"1066","1065":"1065","1086":"1086","1096":"1096","about 1065":"umbes 1065","1060":"1060","England":"England",", , Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1065–":"noin 1065–Kuollut","1060–Male":"1060–Kuollut","1080–Female":"1080–Kuollut","1065–Female":"1065–Kuollut","1080":"1080","1066":"1066","1065":"1065","1086":"1086","1096":"1096","about 1065":"noin 1065","1060":"1060","England":"England",", , Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Somerset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1065–":"environ 1065–Décédée","1060–Male":"1060–Décédé","1080–Female":"1080–Décédée","1065–Female":"1065–Décédée","1080":"1080","1066":"1066","1065":"1065","1086":"1086","1096":"1096","about 1065":"environ 1065","1060":"1060","England":"Angleterre",", , Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Somerset, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Mrs. Joseph est née environ 1065, à Angleterre. Elle a eu au moins 1 fille avec Joseph. Elle est décédée dans sa ville natale."},"de":{"about 1065–":"um 1065–Verstorben","1060–Male":"1060–Verstorben","1080–Female":"1080–Verstorben","1065–Female":"1065–Verstorben","1080":"1080","1066":"1066","1065":"1065","1086":"1086","1096":"1096","about 1065":"u